<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">STATEMENT OF DEFENCE</TI>
<P>1. The Defendant Halifax Regional Municipality (hereinafter called &ldquo;the Defendant&rdquo;) is a municipal corporation pursuant to the authority the <EM>Halifax Regional Municipality Charter</EM>, S.N.S. 2008, c. 39, as amended.</P>
<P>2. The Defendant admits that at all material times hereto, it was responsible for and had control over the construction, maintenance, and upkeep, of the sidewalk running along Veterans Memorial Lane in Halifax, Nova Scotia, including the responsibility for street signage.</P>
<P>3. The Defendant has insufficient knowledge to admit or deny the facts contained in paragraphs 1, 3, 4, 5, and 6, of the Statement of Claim.</P>
<P>4. As to the remainder of the Statement of Claim, the Defendant denies each and every allegation and fact contained therein as if each were set out and traversed and denied <EM>seriatim</EM>, and puts the Plaintiff to the strict proof thereof.</P>
<P>5. The Defendant further states that if the Plaintiff suffered any loss, injury, or damage as alleged (which is not admitted, but denied) such injury, loss, or damage was not caused by the negligence of the Defendant.</P>
<P>6. In addition, or alternatively, the Defendant states that any injury, loss or damage suffered by the Plaintiff (which is not admitted, but denied) was caused by the Plaintiff's own negligence or contributory negligence in that he, <EM>inter alia</EM>:
<P1>a. failed to observe and avoid the area alleged to have a broken sign post;</P1>
<P1>b. failed to manoeuver carefully, or to take any avoiding or precautionary measures to avoid possible injury when he knew or ought to have known the conditions of the sidewalk;</P1>
<P1>c. failed to take reasonable steps or precautions to inform himself of existing conditions;</P1>
<P1>d. failed to operate his wheelchair at a prudent rate of speed having regard to all the conditions and was not giving due care and attention to the condition of the sidewalk then and there prevailing; and</P1>
<P1>e. such other negligence as may appear.</P1></P>
<P>7. The Defendant pleads and relies upon the provisions of the <EM>Contributory Negligence Act</EM>, R.S.N.S. 1989, c. 95 and the <EM>Halifax Regional Municipality Charter</EM>, S.N.S. 2008, c. 39, as amended, including but not limited to s. 377.</P>
<P>8. In addition or alternatively, the Defendant plead pure and simple or inevitable accident.</P>
<P>9. In addition or alternatively, the Defendant states that any injury, loss or damage cl aimed by the Plaintiff (which is not admitted, but denied) was caused or contributed to by other sources or events which either predated or postdated the alleged incident including, <EM>inter alia</EM>, the Plaintiff's prior health history relating to disorders and conditions which existed prior to the accident.</P>
<P>10. The Defendant denies that the Plaintiff suffered any injury, loss or damage as claimed and puts the Plaintiff to the strict proof to the contrary.</P>
<P>11. The Defendant states that if the Plaintiff suffered any injury, loss or damage as alleged (which is not admitted but denied) that the Plaintiff failed to take proper steps to mitigate his alleged loss and puts the Plaintiff to the strict proof to the contrary.</P>
<P>12. The Defendant asks that the Plaintiff's action be dismissed with costs.</P>
<P>DATED at Halifax, Nova Scotia, this 16th day of November, 2015.</P>
