<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT OF DANIEL FORSYTH Sworn on March 15 2017</TI>
<P>I, Daniel Forsyth, of Dartmouth, Nova Scotia, make oath and say as follows:</P>
<P>1. I am the Plaintiff in this proceeding.</P>
<P>2. I have personal knowledge of the evidence sworn to in this affidavit except where otherwise stated to be based on information and belief.</P>
<P>3. I state, in this affidavit, the source of any information that is not based on my own personal knowledge, and state my belief of the source.</P>
<P>4. As a result of injuries sustained in an accident in 2006, I require the use of a wheelchair because the injuries sustained resulted in paraplegia.</P>
<P>5. On April 16, 2015 I was visiting my father. He was a patient at the Queen Elizabeth II Health Sciences Centre.</P>
<P>6. After finishing my visit I exited from the hospital. It was my intention to travel to Spring Garden Road in order to get a bus to return to my home in Dartmouth.</P>
<P>7. Upon exiting the hospital I travelled along the sidewalk of Veterans Memorial Way. My direction of travel was taking me towards Summer Street. The sidewalk is somewhat at a down hill angle as one moves towards Summer Street.</P>
<P>8. There were snow banks on either side of the sidewalk. There was a slight layer of snow on the main travelled portions of the sidewalk.</P>
<P>9. As I progressed towards Summer Street my wheelchair struck something and I was thrown from the wheelchair. I did not and could not see the object that I struck prior to hitting it as it was obscured by the snow.</P>
<P>10. After the accident I realized that the object which I struck was the remnants of a traffic sign which had been broken.</P>
<P>11. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo; is a copy of the Emergency Health Services report dated April 16, 2015. The report includes details with respect to the accident and certain symptoms I was experiencing immediately following the fall.</P>
<P>12. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo; is a copy of a X-ray report dated April 16, 2015. The report indicates that as a result of the fall, I sustained comminuted fractures of my distal femur, proximal tibia and fibula.</P>
<P>13. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;C&rdquo; is a further X-ray report dated October 7, 2015.</P>
<P>14. Between the injuries sustained in 2006 and those sustained as a result of the fall on April 16, 2015, I had other injuries and medical issues. These include medication addiction issues and other physical injuries.</P>
<P>15. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;D&rdquo; is a copy of a report from Dr. John Fraser to Wawanesa Insurance. Dr. Fraser was asked to write a report in relation to injuries I sustained in a motor vehicle accident on January 20, 2013. Dr. Fraser's report addresses matters arising out of my addiction issues, as well as issues arising out of the January 20, 2013 motor vehicle accident. A claim was made as a result of the January 20, 2013 accident and has now been resolved.</P>
<P>16. Since the April 16, 2015 accident I have had other injuries. These include injuries to my ankle and right leg. Attached as Exhibits &ldquo;E&rdquo; and &ldquo;F&rdquo; respectively are copies of an Ambulatory Care Clinic letter written by Dr. Nathan Urquhart on November 16, 2015 and a CT scan report dated March 25, 2016.</P>
<P>17. Through my counsel, Peter Rumscheidt, Stanley Consulting Services was retained to prepare a cost of future care and loss of valuable services life care plan report in support of my claim for compensation in the within proceeding. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;G&rdquo; is a copy of the March 18, 2016 report of Stanley Consulting Services.</P>
<P>18. The Notice of Action and Statement of Claim in this matter was filed with the Court on October 5, 2015. The Notice of Defence on behalf of the Defendant was filed on November 16, 2015.</P>
<P>19. I have provided to the Defendant an original Affidavit Disclosing Documents as well as two Supplemental Affidavits Disclosing Documents. These Affidavits include a very large volume of medical records from both before and after the April 16, 2015 accident. The Defendant has provided its original Affidavit Disclosing Documents as well as a Supplementary Affidavit Disclosing Affidavits.</P>
<P>20. Discovery examinations of me and a representative of the Defendant took place on October 27, 2016.</P>
<P>21. I am advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that on December 5, 2016 he filed with the Court a Request for Date Assignment Conference. I am further advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that on December 13, 2016 the Defendant filed its Memorandum for Date Assignment Judge.</P>
<P>22. I am advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that a Date Assignment Conference call was scheduled for March 3, 2017.</P>
<P>23. Following review with Mr. Rumscheidt, I provided him with instructions to explore with counsel for the Defendant whether the Defendant would consent to conducting a trial of the liability question in this matter separate from a trial with respect to the damages question. I am advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that counsel for the Defendant advised her client was not prepared to consent to such an agreement.</P>
<P>24. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;H&rdquo; is a copy of correspondence from my counsel to the Scheduling Office of this Court dated February 27, 2017.</P>
<P>25. I am advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that in response to his February 27, 2017 letter, the Court advised that the issue of whether the matters of liability and damages should be tried at a separate time would need to be the subject matter of a formal motion to the Court.</P>
<P>26. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo; is a copy of an email from Matthew Dunn dated May 5, 2016 addressed to Roxanne Maclaurin and Desmond Munden (&ldquo;Mr. Munden&rdquo;).</P>
<P>27. Mr. Munden was the representative of the Defendant who was discovered by Mr. Rumscheidt on October 27, 2016.</P>
<P>28. I am advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that during the course of Mr. Munden's discovery examination he confirmed that the contents of Exhibit &ldquo;I&rdquo; represent the results of the Defendant's investigation into the April 16, 2015 incident.</P>
<P>29. Among the conclusions reached in the investigation summary was the location of the broken traffic post which I struck on April 16, 2015. I accept as accurate that conclusion.</P>
<P>30. One of the other conclusions reached in the investigation summary was that a broken sign which had been responded to prior to my accident by employees of the Defendant was different from the sign involved in my incident. I accept as accurate that conclusion.</P>
<P>31. Attached as Exhibit &ldquo;J&rdquo; is an extract from the discovery transcript for Mr. Munden. The extract includes Mr. Munden's evidence that having reviewed all of the circumstances, the Defendant's conclusion is that the post involved in my accident was knocked over by snow plowing efforts at some point between August 2014 and the date of my accident.</P>
<P>32. I am advised by Mr. Rumscheidt and believe that he has received confirmation from counsel for the Defendant that at all relevant times, snow clearing efforts on Veterans Memorial Way were undertaken by employees of the Defendant.</P>
<P>33. Based on communications with Mr. Rumscheidt, I strongly expect that, in support of my claim for damages, I will be retaining at least one and perhaps two additional experts f or purposes of preparing reports. In particular, it is anticipated that an expert in orthopaedics and/or an expert in physical medical and rehabilitation may be retained.</P>
<P>34. Given the on-going medical issues I face as a result of the 2006 accident as well as matters that have arisen since, including the April 14, 2015 accident, I anticipate I may be limited with respect to how long I could stay in the witness stand to given evidence at a trial. I anticipate that I may need more frequent breaks than might be the normal procedure.</P>
